&lt;p&gt;CRN EAST MIDLANDS&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;RESEARCH SUPPORT TEAM (NORTHAMPTONSHIRE HUB)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The University Hospitals of Leicester NHS Trust is the host organisation for the Clinical Research Network East Midlands (CRN EM), one of the 15 LCRNs across England, which form part of the National Institute for Health Research Clinical Research Network. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;CRN East Midlands are now recruiting to its flexible workforce.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Are you a registered nurse with Clinical Research experience, either in a research nurse post ,or as an additional responsibility within a nursing role? Would you like to further develop your career in research? An exciting opportunity has arisen for an individual to be a part of the CRN: East Midlands Research Support Team (Northamptonshire Hub). This post will give you the opportunity to broaden your research skills and knowledge within differing specialties across the health and social care sector. We are seeking to appoint a Research Nurse to be part of a small team of research staff, The post holder will be based at Albany House Medical Centre Wellingborough, however extensive travel across Northamptonshire will be expected, and some travel across the East Midlands will be required.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Katie Warwick - RST Hub Lead (Northamptonshire)&lt;/p&gt;
